Distribution . West Atlantic: USA (Gulf of Mexico to North Carolina), Mexico , Belize , Panama ( Bocas del Toro , Bahía de Caledonia), Bahamas , Cuba , Jamaica , Puerto Rico , N and E Lesser Antilles, Colombia , Venezuela , Guyana , Suriname , French Guyana , Brazil and Uruguay (Holthuis 1959; Haig 1966; Gore 1982 ; Williams 1984 ; Ferreira & Melo 2016 ; Poupin 2018 ;
Mantelatto et al . 2021
).

Remarks .
Porcellana sayana
is one of the most colourful and “charismatic” western Atlantic porcelain crabs, well known to divers and underwater photographers (e.g.
Humann et al. 2013
). Haig (1966) already noted a remarkable variation in the colour pattern of the species, with most individuals covered by white or lavender-coloured rounded spots of various sizes, some with dark red circle; others have longitudinal bands or combine spots and bands ( Williams 1984 ;
Lira et al. 2012
;
Humann et al. 2013
;
Mendonça et al. 2019
;
Mantelatto et al . 2021
). The chromatic variation of
P. sayana
is exemplified by our single Panamanian specimen ( Fig. 83 ) and several specimens from Florida ( Figs. 85 , 91C ). The Panamanian specimen, which seems to be a relatively young male, was found in association with
P. diogenes
, one of the most common hosts of this porcelain crab ( Fig. 84 ).
